{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LpuyntS16knaLtZjQj24g8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have gathered comprehensive information. Let me create a summary document of all the findings:\n\n## Summary: Log Storage and Display System in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly explored the log storage and display system across the Cloche codebase. Here's a complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Raw Log Format (Claude Code Streaming Output)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n\nThe raw logs are stored in a **unified text log format** at:\n```\n<project-dir>/.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log\n```\n\n**Format:** `[RFC3339 Timestamp] [EntryType] Content`\n\nExample:\n```\n[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:01Z] [script] npm run build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:02Z] [llm] Claude: I'll start by reading the relevant files...\n```\n\n**Entry Types** (defined as `EntryType` enum):\n- `TypeStatus = \"status\"` - Workflow status updates (step started/completed)\n- `TypeScript = \"script\"` - Script execution output\n- `TypeLLM = \"llm\"` - LLM/Claude output\n\nMulti-line messages are automatically split into separate entries with the same timestamp.\n\n---\n\n### **2. JSON Protocol Messages (Container Output)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`\n\nThe agent container outputs **JSON-lines format** status messages that the gRPC server parses:\n\n```go\ntype StatusMessage struct {\n    Type      MessageType `json:\"type\"`       // \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"log\", \"error\"\n    StepName  string      `json:\"step_name,omitempty\"`\n    Result    string      `json:\"result,omitempty\"`\n    Message   string      `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n    Timestamp time.Time   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n```\n\nExample JSON messages from container:\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"build\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T10:15:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"log\",\"message\":\"Claude: Starting analysis\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T10:15:01Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"build\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T10:15:02Z\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **3. Log Storage System**\n\n**Three-layer storage approach:**\n\n#### **A. Live Streaming (In-Memory Broadcaster)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n\n- **Purpose:** Real-time streaming to active clients\n- **Type:** `LogLine` struct\n  ```go\n  type LogLine struct {\n      Timestamp string `json:\"timestamp\"` // RFC3339\n      Type      string `json:\"type\"`      // \"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n      Content   string `json:\"content\"`   // the log message\n  }\n  ```\n- **Implementation:** Thread-safe broadcaster with per-run subscribers\n- **Channel Buffer:** 256 entries per subscriber\n- **Drop Policy:** Non-blocking; slow subscribers get dropped messages\n- **Lifecycle:** Marked \"done\" when run completes, closes all subscriber channels\n\n#### **B. Persistent File Storage**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 273-286)\n\nAfter a run completes:\n1. Full `full.log` written to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log`\n2. Per-step outputs extracted to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.log`\n3. Container stdout/stderr captured to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/container.log`\n4. Full container logs saved for debugging\n\n#### **C. Indexed Log Store (SQLite)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 87-96, 301-342)\n\n**Database Schema:**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE log_files (\n    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n    step_name TEXT,\n    file_type TEXT NOT NULL,      -- \"full\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    file_path TEXT NOT NULL,       -- absolute path\n    file_size INTEGER,\n    created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n    FOREIGN KEY (run_id) REFERENCES runs(id)\n)\n```\n\n**LogStore Interface Methods:**\n- `SaveLogFile(ctx, entry)` - Index a log file\n- `GetLogFiles(ctx, runID)` - All logs for a run\n- `GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, runID, stepName)` - Logs for specific step\n- `GetLogFileByType(ctx, runID, fileType)` - Logs of specific type\n\n---\n\n### **4. How Logs are Currently Displayed**\n\n#### **A. Server-Side Log Streaming (Handler)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 713-815)\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` (Server-Sent Events)\n\n**For Active Runs:**\n- Subscribes to live `logstream.Broadcaster`\n- Streams each `LogLine` as a JSON SSE event\n- Sends `event: done` when run completes\n\n**For Completed Runs:**\n1. Reads `full.log` from disk\n2. Parses each line with regex: `^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`\n3. Converts to `LogLine` JSON\n4. Streams as SSE events\n\n**Fallback Parsing:** For unstructured lines (no regex match), defaults to type=\"script\"\n\n#### **B. Client-Side Log Display (JavaScript)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 69-237)\n\n**HTML Structure:**\n```html\n<h2>\n    Log\n    <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\">Live</span>\n</h2>\n<div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\">\n    <pre id=\"log-content\"></pre>\n</div>\n```\n\n**JavaScript Functionality:**\n- Connects to `/api/runs/{runID}/stream` via `EventSource` (SSE)\n- Parses each JSON line: `line = JSON.parse(e.data)`\n- Creates `<span class=\"log-line log-type-{type}\">` for each entry\n- Displays as: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n- Auto-scrolls when user is at bottom (scrollHeight detection)\n- Updates badge from \"Live\" to \"Complete\" when stream ends\n- CSS styling varies by type: `.log-type-status`, `.log-type-script`, `.log-type-llm`\n\n#### **C. Step Output Handler**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 563-634)\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output?type=script|llm`\n\nLookup order:\n1. Check log index (if available) - fast lookup\n2. Try per-step file: `{outputDir}/{step}.log`\n3. Fall back to full container log: `{outputDir}/container.log`\n4. Last resort: live Docker logs from running container\n\n---\n\n### **5. Domain Types Related to Logs**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string        // step identifier\n    Result      string        // \"success\", \"fail\", etc.\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string        // historically stored per-step logs\n    GitRef      string        // output git ref\n}\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState     // pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string\n    ContainerKept  bool\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **6. Web Dashboard Log Display**\n\n**Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\n**Features:**\n- Live streaming with SSE connection\n- Auto-scroll when user is at the bottom\n- Manual scroll disables auto-scroll\n- Badge status indicator (Live → Complete)\n- Log viewer in scrollable `<pre>` element\n- Color-coded by type through CSS classes\n- Step execution table above logs showing:\n  - Step name\n  - Result (success/fail badge)\n  - Started time\n  - Duration\n\n**Step Output Toggle:**\n- Clicking a step row expands/collapses detailed output\n- Lazily loads from `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Can be filtered by type (`?type=script` or `?type=llm`)\n\n---\n\n### **7. Key Integration Points**\n\n**Logging Flow:**\n1. Agent container emits JSON status messages to stdout\n2. gRPC server (server.go:211-227) parses JSON messages\n3. `MsgLog` messages published to live `Broadcaster`\n4. Web clients receive via SSE, render in real-time\n5. On run completion, `full.log` written to disk\n6. Future accesses read and stream from disk\n\n**Storage Lifecycle:**\n1. During run: Logs kept in memory (broadcaster)\n2. At completion: Extracted to disk files\n3. Optional: Indexed in SQLite for fast lookups\n4. Web handler prioritizes index, falls back to file reads\n\n---\n\n### **Key Files Summary**\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` | Disk-based log writer with timestamping |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` | In-memory log broadcaster for active runs |\n| `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` | JSON status message format from agent |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Parses agent output, publishes to broadcaster |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Log file indexing in database |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | SSE streaming endpoint, log parsing, fallback paths |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` | Client-side log UI and SSE consumer |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run and StepExecution domain models |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | LogStore interface definition |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a42a63ccbccb17355 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74157\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 64683</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65a45440-8ea2-48ce-9346-c9049e4bd586","uuid":"5e1f8dae-d3f3-4382-bfcc-ea3821342a62","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how logs are stored and displayed in this Go project. Explore:\n\n1. The web dashboard templates and handlers in internal/adapters/web/ - especially how run logs are displayed\n2. The log store in internal/logstream/ - how logs are stored and retrieved\n3. Any existing JSON parsing of Claude Code output\n4. The domain types related to logs/runs\n\nBe very thorough. Read the full contents of key files. I need to understand:\n- What format the raw JSON log entries are in (Claude Code streaming output)\n- How they're currently stored\n- How they're currently displayed in the web UI\n- What the template looks like for log display\n\nFocus on these paths:\n- internal/logstream/\n- internal/adapters/web/handler.go (especially log-related handlers)\n- internal/adapters/web/templates/ (especially any log/run detail templates)\n- internal/domain/ types related to logs","agentId":"a42a63ccbccb17355","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have gathered comprehensive information. Let me create a summary document of all the findings:\n\n## Summary: Log Storage and Display System in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly explored the log storage and display system across the Cloche codebase. Here's a complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Raw Log Format (Claude Code Streaming Output)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n\nThe raw logs are stored in a **unified text log format** at:\n```\n<project-dir>/.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log\n```\n\n**Format:** `[RFC3339 Timestamp] [EntryType] Content`\n\nExample:\n```\n[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:01Z] [script] npm run build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:02Z] [llm] Claude: I'll start by reading the relevant files...\n```\n\n**Entry Types** (defined as `EntryType` enum):\n- `TypeStatus = \"status\"` - Workflow status updates (step started/completed)\n- `TypeScript = \"script\"` - Script execution output\n- `TypeLLM = \"llm\"` - LLM/Claude output\n\nMulti-line messages are automatically split into separate entries with the same timestamp.\n\n---\n\n### **2. JSON Protocol Messages (Container Output)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`\n\nThe agent container outputs **JSON-lines format** status messages that the gRPC server parses:\n\n```go\ntype StatusMessage struct {\n    Type      MessageType `json:\"type\"`       // \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"log\", \"error\"\n    StepName  string      `json:\"step_name,omitempty\"`\n    Result    string      `json:\"result,omitempty\"`\n    Message   string      `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n    Timestamp time.Time   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n```\n\nExample JSON messages from container:\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"build\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T10:15:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"log\",\"message\":\"Claude: Starting analysis\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T10:15:01Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"build\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T10:15:02Z\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **3. Log Storage System**\n\n**Three-layer storage approach:**\n\n#### **A. Live Streaming (In-Memory Broadcaster)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n\n- **Purpose:** Real-time streaming to active clients\n- **Type:** `LogLine` struct\n  ```go\n  type LogLine struct {\n      Timestamp string `json:\"timestamp\"` // RFC3339\n      Type      string `json:\"type\"`      // \"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n      Content   string `json:\"content\"`   // the log message\n  }\n  ```\n- **Implementation:** Thread-safe broadcaster with per-run subscribers\n- **Channel Buffer:** 256 entries per subscriber\n- **Drop Policy:** Non-blocking; slow subscribers get dropped messages\n- **Lifecycle:** Marked \"done\" when run completes, closes all subscriber channels\n\n#### **B. Persistent File Storage**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 273-286)\n\nAfter a run completes:\n1. Full `full.log` written to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log`\n2. Per-step outputs extracted to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.log`\n3. Container stdout/stderr captured to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/container.log`\n4. Full container logs saved for debugging\n\n#### **C. Indexed Log Store (SQLite)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 87-96, 301-342)\n\n**Database Schema:**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE log_files (\n    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n    step_name TEXT,\n    file_type TEXT NOT NULL,      -- \"full\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    file_path TEXT NOT NULL,       -- absolute path\n    file_size INTEGER,\n    created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n    FOREIGN KEY (run_id) REFERENCES runs(id)\n)\n```\n\n**LogStore Interface Methods:**\n- `SaveLogFile(ctx, entry)` - Index a log file\n- `GetLogFiles(ctx, runID)` - All logs for a run\n- `GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, runID, stepName)` - Logs for specific step\n- `GetLogFileByType(ctx, runID, fileType)` - Logs of specific type\n\n---\n\n### **4. How Logs are Currently Displayed**\n\n#### **A. Server-Side Log Streaming (Handler)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 713-815)\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` (Server-Sent Events)\n\n**For Active Runs:**\n- Subscribes to live `logstream.Broadcaster`\n- Streams each `LogLine` as a JSON SSE event\n- Sends `event: done` when run completes\n\n**For Completed Runs:**\n1. Reads `full.log` from disk\n2. Parses each line with regex: `^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`\n3. Converts to `LogLine` JSON\n4. Streams as SSE events\n\n**Fallback Parsing:** For unstructured lines (no regex match), defaults to type=\"script\"\n\n#### **B. Client-Side Log Display (JavaScript)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 69-237)\n\n**HTML Structure:**\n```html\n<h2>\n    Log\n    <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\">Live</span>\n</h2>\n<div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\">\n    <pre id=\"log-content\"></pre>\n</div>\n```\n\n**JavaScript Functionality:**\n- Connects to `/api/runs/{runID}/stream` via `EventSource` (SSE)\n- Parses each JSON line: `line = JSON.parse(e.data)`\n- Creates `<span class=\"log-line log-type-{type}\">` for each entry\n- Displays as: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n- Auto-scrolls when user is at bottom (scrollHeight detection)\n- Updates badge from \"Live\" to \"Complete\" when stream ends\n- CSS styling varies by type: `.log-type-status`, `.log-type-script`, `.log-type-llm`\n\n#### **C. Step Output Handler**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 563-634)\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output?type=script|llm`\n\nLookup order:\n1. Check log index (if available) - fast lookup\n2. Try per-step file: `{outputDir}/{step}.log`\n3. Fall back to full container log: `{outputDir}/container.log`\n4. Last resort: live Docker logs from running container\n\n---\n\n### **5. Domain Types Related to Logs**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string        // step identifier\n    Result      string        // \"success\", \"fail\", etc.\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string        // historically stored per-step logs\n    GitRef      string        // output git ref\n}\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState     // pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string\n    ContainerKept  bool\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **6. Web Dashboard Log Display**\n\n**Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\n**Features:**\n- Live streaming with SSE connection\n- Auto-scroll when user is at the bottom\n- Manual scroll disables auto-scroll\n- Badge status indicator (Live → Complete)\n- Log viewer in scrollable `<pre>` element\n- Color-coded by type through CSS classes\n- Step execution table above logs showing:\n  - Step name\n  - Result (success/fail badge)\n  - Started time\n  - Duration\n\n**Step Output Toggle:**\n- Clicking a step row expands/collapses detailed output\n- Lazily loads from `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Can be filtered by type (`?type=script` or `?type=llm`)\n\n---\n\n### **7. Key Integration Points**\n\n**Logging Flow:**\n1. Agent container emits JSON status messages to stdout\n2. gRPC server (server.go:211-227) parses JSON messages\n3. `MsgLog` messages published to live `Broadcaster`\n4. Web clients receive via SSE, render in real-time\n5. On run completion, `full.log` written to disk\n6. Future accesses read and stream from disk\n\n**Storage Lifecycle:**\n1. During run: Logs kept in memory (broadcaster)\n2. At completion: Extracted to disk files\n3. Optional: Indexed in SQLite for fast lookups\n4. Web handler prioritizes index, falls back to file reads\n\n---\n\n### **Key Files Summary**\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` | Disk-based log writer with timestamping |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` | In-memory log broadcaster for active runs |\n| `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` | JSON status message format from agent |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Parses agent output, publishes to broadcaster |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Log file indexing in database |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | SSE streaming endpoint, log parsing, fallback paths |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` | Client-side log UI and SSE consumer |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run and StepExecution domain models |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | LogStore interface definition |"}],"totalDurationMs":64683,"totalTokens":74157,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":653,"cache_read_input_tokens":70895,"output_tokens":2609,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":653},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
