{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MKPgL4TBZaAEBcBodYs6kw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the complete picture:\n\n1. **In the agent container**: After a step completes, `logStepOutput()` is called. For agent/prompt steps, it reads the raw `{step}.log` file (which contains ALL raw Claude Code stream-json output) and writes each line to `full.log` with `[llm]` type prefix. So the `full.log` contains the raw Claude Code JSON for each line.\n\n2. **For live runs**: The `StatusWriter.Log()` sends extracted text content (from `extractStreamText()`) via the status protocol to the daemon. The daemon publishes these as `LogLine{Type: \"llm\", Content: <extracted text>}`. So **live runs already show human-readable text**.\n\n\n3. **For completed runs**: The web handler reads `full.log`, parses lines with the regex, and sends them as SSE events. The `[llm]` lines contain the raw JSON, so **completed runs show raw JSON**. The fix is to format the content of `[llm]` entries when reading from `full.log` for completed runs, and handle the same for the step output handler. Looking at the sample full.log content, the llm entries are raw JSON objects that need to be extracted and formatted into readable text. I'm outlining the implementation plan: I'll create a formatting function in the logstream package that parses the JSON log entries and extracts the relevant content based on message type, then integrate it into the web handler to filter and display only the meaningful log lines while keeping the raw logs untouched for debugging.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2566,"cache_read_input_tokens":86161,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2566},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65a45440-8ea2-48ce-9346-c9049e4bd586","uuid":"6cab8062-41ad-4924-b55c-558f75324691"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MKPgL4TBZaAEBcBodYs6kw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. The issue is clear:\n\n- **Live runs**: The agent adapter already extracts text via `extractStreamText()` before sending — these are already human-readable.\n- **Completed runs**: The `full.log` file stores raw Claude Code stream-json, and the web handler serves it as-is via SSE.\n\nI need to add a formatting layer that parses the raw JSON `[llm]` entries from `full.log` and extracts readable content.\n\nLet me implement this."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2566,"cache_read_input_tokens":86161,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2566},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65a45440-8ea2-48ce-9346-c9049e4bd586","uuid":"9aba026f-a977-4d5a-b363-baee700fb564"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MKPgL4TBZaAEBcBodYs6kw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Tz9B56PqNJjdqQVMTykpLM","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/internal/logstream/format.go","content":"package logstream\n\nimport (\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"strings\"\n)\n\n// FormatLLMContent parses a raw Claude Code stream-json line and returns\n// human-readable text. Returns empty string for entries that should be skipped\n// (system init, rate limits, thinking blocks, tool results).\nfunc FormatLLMContent(raw string) string {\n\tvar event map[string]json.RawMessage\n\tif json.Unmarshal([]byte(raw), &event) != nil {\n\t\treturn raw // not JSON, return as-is\n\t}\n\n\tvar typ string\n\tif t, ok := event[\"type\"]; ok {\n\t\tjson.Unmarshal(t, &typ)\n\t}\n\n\tswitch typ {\n\tcase \"assistant\":\n\t\treturn formatAssistantEvent(event)\n\tcase \"result\":\n\t\treturn formatResultEvent(event)\n\tcase \"system\", \"rate_limit_event\", \"user\":\n\t\treturn \"\" // skip\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn raw\n\t}\n}\n\n// formatAssistantEvent extracts text and tool_use content from assistant messages.\nfunc formatAssistantEvent(event map[string]json.RawMessage) string {\n\tmsgRaw, ok := event[\"message\"]\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\n\tvar msg struct {\n\t\tContent []struct {\n\t\t\tType  string          `json:\"type\"`\n\t\t\tText  string          `json:\"text\"`\n\t\t\tName  string          `json:\"name\"`\n\t\t\tInput json.RawMessage `json:\"input\"`\n\t\t} `json:\"content\"`\n\t}\n\tif json.Unmarshal(msgRaw, &msg) != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\n\tvar parts []string\n\tfor _, block := range msg.Content {\n\t\tswitch block.Type {\n\t\tcase \"text\":\n\t\t\tif block.Text != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tparts = append(parts, block.Text)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"tool_use\":\n\t\t\tparts = append(parts, formatToolUse(block.Name, block.Input))\n\t\t}\n\t\t// skip \"thinking\" blocks\n\t}\n\n\tif len(parts) == 0 {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\treturn strings.Join(parts, \"\\n\")\n}\n\n// formatToolUse produces a concise summary of a tool call.\nfunc formatToolUse(name string, inputRaw json.RawMessage) string {\n\tvar input map[string]any\n\tjson.Unmarshal(inputRaw, &input)\n\n\tswitch name {\n\tcase \"Read\":\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ Read %s\", strVal(input, \"file_path\"))\n\tcase \"Edit\":\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ Edit %s\", strVal(input, \"file_path\"))\n\tcase \"Write\":\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ Write %s\", strVal(input, \"file_path\"))\n\tcase \"Bash\":\n\t\tcmd := strVal(input, \"command\")\n\t\tif len(cmd) > 120 {\n\t\t\tcmd = cmd[:120] + \"...\"\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ Bash: %s\", cmd)\n\tcase \"Grep\":\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ Grep: %s\", strVal(input, \"pattern\"))\n\tcase \"Glob\":\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ Glob: %s\", strVal(input, \"pattern\"))\n\tcase \"Agent\":\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ Agent: %s\", strVal(input, \"description\"))\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"⚙ %s\", name)\n\t}\n}\n\n// formatResultEvent produces a summary of the final result event.\nfunc formatResultEvent(event map[string]json.RawMessage) string {\n\tvar subtype, result string\n\tjson.Unmarshal(event[\"subtype\"], &subtype)\n\tjson.Unmarshal(event[\"result\"], &result)\n\n\tvar durationMs float64\n\tjson.Unmarshal(event[\"duration_ms\"], &durationMs)\n\n\tvar numTurns float64\n\tjson.Unmarshal(event[\"num_turns\"], &numTurns)\n\n\tvar costUSD float64\n\tjson.Unmarshal(event[\"total_cost_usd\"], &costUSD)\n\n\tvar parts []string\n\tparts = append(parts, fmt.Sprintf(\"── Result: %s\", subtype))\n\tif numTurns > 0 {\n\t\tparts = append(parts, fmt.Sprintf(\"   %d turns\", int(numTurns)))\n\t}\n\tif durationMs > 0 {\n\t\tparts = append(parts, fmt.Sprintf(\"   %.1fs\", durationMs/1000))\n\t}\n\tif costUSD > 0 {\n\t\tparts = append(parts, fmt.Sprintf(\"   $%.4f\", costUSD))\n\t}\n\treturn strings.Join(parts, \" |\")\n}\n\nfunc strVal(m map[string]any, key string) string {\n\tif m == nil {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\tv, _ := m[key].(string)\n\treturn v\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2566,"cache_read_input_tokens":86161,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2566},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65a45440-8ea2-48ce-9346-c9049e4bd586","uuid":"df2e8b11-9bd6-4bf8-b292-9ef1ff2f0dcd"}
