{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DXXQSsRNNoypbhz3ht5C9o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me modify the web handler. There are two places to modify:\n\n1. `streamFullLog` - reads `full.log` and streams as SSE events. I need to apply formatting and skip empty entries.\n2. `handleAPIStream` live path - the live content is already extracted text, so it should be fine. But let me still apply formatting there for consistency.\n\nActually wait - for live runs, the content published to the broadcaster is the extracted text from `StatusWriter.Log()`. These are already plain text lines. So I don't need to format those. I only need to format the archived `full.log` content.\n\nBut looking more carefully at the gRPC server code (server.go:218-226):\n\n\nThe `msg.Message` here is a single text line from `extractStreamText()`. So it's already human-readable for live runs. For completed runs, the `full.log` contains the raw JSON, so I need to modify `streamFullLog` to parse and extract the text content before streaming it.\n\nI think the cleanest approach is to handle the formatting in `streamFullLog` itself, where I can filter out entries that produce empty content after extraction. I should also consider the step output handler for agent steps, but the task is specifically about the run log view, so I'll focus on that first.\n\nLooking at how step outputs work, each raw JSON line from the Claude Code stream gets written as a separate timestamped entry in the full log. I can format each one individually in the streaming handler.\n\nModifying the streaming function... Finishing the log streaming function...\n\nNow I'm thinking about how to handle the step output handler too. When someone clicks on a step and sees the raw JSON, I should apply the same formatting there. I could create a helper function to process entire files line-by-line, but keeping it simple makes more sense—just apply the formatting if the file contains raw JSON. Let me implement these changes now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1215,"cache_read_input_tokens":90894,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1215},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65a45440-8ea2-48ce-9346-c9049e4bd586","uuid":"6d5409d7-bb0b-4035-b1dc-c0e3ff14f742"}
